## How to read this

- **Top tier** (🟥 Core, 🟧 Supporting, 🟦 H2): the **strategic
  classification** — what differentiates from competitors vs what enables vs
  what is deferred.
- **Sub-capabilities** below each core box are the concrete things that
  capability *does* — each maps to specific bounded-context logic.
- **Italic text** on each box is the bounded context name in
  `6-contexts/` nomenclature, so engineers can cross-reference.

